Aspects of Scientific Explanation and other Essays in the Philosophy of Science is a 1965 book by Carl Gustav Hempel , regarded as one of the most important works in philosophy of science written after the Second World War .
`` New Rose Hotel '' is a short story by William Gibson , first published in 1984 in Omni and later included in his 1986 collection Burning Chrome .
`` The Hound of Heaven '' is a 182-line poem written by English poet Francis Thompson ( 1859 - -1907 ) .
Searching for Dragons is a young adult fantasy novel by Patricia Wrede , second in the Enchanted Forest Chronicles , about a young princess who lives with dragons and leads an unusual life .
A Fish in the Water ( originally published as El pez en el agua in 1993 ) , is the memoir of Peruvian writer Mario Vargas Llosa , who won the Nobel Prize in Literature in 2010 .
Gandhi Under Cross Examination is a 2009 book written by G. B. Singh and Dr. Tim Watson evaluating the iconization of Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi as a civil rights protagonist In 1893 Gandhi went to South Africa where , according to his own account , he was thrown off of a train on racial grounds .
Sunwing is a children 's book written in 1999 by Canadian author Kenneth Oppel .
The Mislaid Charm is a fantasy novel by author Alexander M. Phillips .
In the Year of Jubilee is the thirteenth novel by English author George Gissing .
Wonder under Water is the English - language title of German film director Leni Riefenstahl 's 1990 Wunder unter Wasser , an illustrations book of marine life .
`` The Monkey '' is a short story by Stephen King , first published in Gallery magazine in 1980 .
Storm of Steel ( in German : In Stahlgewittern , ISBN 0 - 86527 - 310 - 3 ) is the memoir of German officer Ernst Jünger 's experiences on the Western Front during the First World War .
Gnorm Gnat was an American gag - a - day comic strip by Jim Davis based on fictional insects , especially a gnat named Gnorm .
The Rhesus Chart ( 2014 ) is the fifth novel by Charles Stross in his `` Laundry '' series of Lovecraftian spy thrillers .
The Luminaries is the second novel by Eleanor Catton , published by Victoria University Press in August 2013 and Granta on 5 September 2013 .
Up Above the World is a novel by Paul Bowles first published in 1966 about an American couple -- an aging physician and his young attractive wife -- who go on a tour of Central America and are trapped by a mysterious young man whose motives remain unclear to them .
Devil of a State is a 1961 novel by Anthony Burgess based on his experience living and working in Bandar Seri Begawan in the Southeast Asian sultanate of Brunei , on the island of Borneo , in 1958 - 59 .
Hideous Kinky is an autobiographical novel by Esther Freud , daughter of British painter Lucian Freud and great - granddaughter of Sigmund Freud .
Our Sunshine is a 1991 novel about Ned Kelly by Australian writer Robert Drewe .
The Stone Key is a 2008 science fiction novel by Isobelle Carmody , set in a post apocalyptic world .
`` The Man Child '' is a 1965 short story by James Baldwin , taken from the short story collection , Going to Meet the Man .
Poetic Meter and Poetic Form is a book by Paul Fussell , published by McGraw Hill in 1965 , and later as a revised edition in 1979 ( ISBN 0 - 07 - 553606 - 4 ) .
Be Like Water ( 2008 ) is a play written by Dan Kwong , originally produced at East West Players , in association with Cedar Grove OnStage .
The True Confessions of Charlotte Doyle is a historical fiction novel by the American author Avi published in 1990 .
Ring of Fire II is a 2008 anthology created by editor - author - historian Eric Flint .
Daughter of the Empire is a political fantasy novel by Raymond E. Feist and Janny Wurts .
Flowers for Hitler is Canadian poet and composer Leonard Cohen 's third collection of poetry , first published in 1964 by McClelland and Stewart .
Honor of the Clan is a novel by John Ringo and Julie Cochrane , and is part of the Legacy of the Aldenata series , specifically a spin - off that features Michael O'Neal 's daughters Cally and Michelle .
Plan for Chaos is a science fiction novel by John Wyndham first published in 2009 .
The Brass Check is a muckraking exposé of American journalism by Upton Sinclair published in 1919 .
The Song of Kahunsha ( ISBN 0 - 385 - 66228 - 9 ) is a novel by the Indian - Canadian novelist and playwright Anosh Irani , published in 2006 by Doubleday Canada and in 2007 in the US by Milkweed Editions .
Young Gabby Goose is a 1975 anthology of 14 animal - centered fairy tales from around the world , collected and retold by Ruth Manning - Sanders .
Al - Bayan Fi Tafsir al - Quran ( The Elucidation of the Exegesis of The Qur'an and sometimes entitled The Prolegomena to the Quran ) is a tafsir by the Shiite scholar Abu al - Qasim al - Khoei .
Jedi Twilight is the first book in Michael Reaves ' series Coruscant Nights , set in the Dark Times .
A Secular Agenda ( ISBN 81 - 900199 - 3 - 7 ) is a 1997 book by Arun Shourie .
Dragonhaven is a fantasy novel written by Robin McKinley , published by Putnam in 2007 .
You Know I Ca n't Hear You When the Water 's Running is a collection of four unrelated one - act comedy plays by Robert Anderson .
The Imaginary Invalid ( French : Le malade imaginaire ( lə malad imaʒinɛːʁ ) ) is a three - act comédie - ballet by the French playwright Molière with dance sequences and musical interludes by Marc - Antoine Charpentier .
The Border Trilogy consists of three novels by American author Cormac McCarthy :
Fourth Reich of the Rich is a book by self - styled Christian writer Des Griffin about the so - called New World Order .
The Invincible ( Polish : Niezwyciężony ) is a science fiction novel written by Stanisław Lem and published in 1964 .
Skin Folk is a story collection by writer Nalo Hopkinson .
Terminator Gene is the second book in Ian Irvine 's Eco - thriller titles .
The Ninth Man is a novel set in World War II , written by John Lee , inspired by factual events , and set in the United States .
Soft ! is a novel by British writer Rupert Thomson , written in 1998 London .
Lincoln the Unknown is a biography on Abraham Lincoln , written in 1932 by Dale Carnegie .
Walk the Wild Road , earlier titled The Road from Home , is a novel by Nigel Hinton .
The Man Who Loved Clowns is a 1992 novel by June Rae Wood about coping with mental disability in the family .
Tommy Storm and the Galactic Knights is the second novel in the Tommy Storm series , written by Irish author A.J. Healy .
Grimus is a 1975 fantasy and science fiction novel by Salman Rushdie .
Etiquette & Espionage is a young adult steampunk novel by Gail Carriger .
Coffee , Tea or Me ? is a book of alleged memoirs by the fictitious stewardesses Trudy Baker and Rachel Jones , written by the initially uncredited Donald Bain and first published in 1967 .
A British Picture ( ISBN 978 - 1 - 904915 - 32 - 4 , 2008 ) is the autobiography of the English film director Ken Russell .
A Beautiful Blue Death , by Charles Finch , is the first novel in a series of mysteries featuring Victorian gentleman and amateur detective Charles Lenox .
Bersøglis- og andre Viser is a poetry collection published by Norwegian poet Per Sivle in 1895 .
The Red Gods ( French : Les dieux rouges ) is an adventure novel with elements of fantasy , written by French writer Jean d'Esme , published in 1924 .
Ravensong is a novel written by the contemporary Canadian author , Lee Maracle .
A Deadly Secret , also translated as Requiem of Ling Sing and Secret of the Linked Cities , is a wuxia novel by Jin Yong ( Louis Cha ) .
Marx and Modern Economics is a 1968 book about Karl Marx edited by David Horowitz .
The Tiger Who Came to Tea is a short children 's story , first published in 1968 , written and illustrated by Judith Kerr .
Johnny Tremain is a 1943 children 's fiction historical novel by Esther Forbes set in Boston prior to and during the outbreak of the American Revolution .
The Light of Asia , subtitled The Great Renunciation , is a book by Sir Edwin Arnold .
Asimov 's Guide to Shakespeare , by Isaac Asimov , vols I and II ( 1970 ) , ISBN 978 - 0 - 517 - 26825 - 4 ;
The Fort at River 's Bend is a 1997 historical novel by Canadian novelist Jack Whyte .
Man 's Hope ( French : L'Espoir ) is a 1937 novel by André Malraux based upon his experiences in the Spanish Civil War .
Theory of Colours ( original German title Zur Farbenlehre ) is a book by Johann Wolfgang von Goethe about the poet 's views on the nature of colours and how these are perceived by humans .
The Drowned and the Saved ( 1986 ) is a book of essays on life in the Nazi Vernichtungslager ( extermination camps ) by Italian - Jewish author and Holocaust survivor Primo Levi , drawing on his personal experience as an inmate of Auschwitz .
The London Eye Mystery is a children 's mystery novel by English author Siobhan Dowd .
Social Outsiders in Nazi Germany is a book edited by Robert Gellately and Nathan Stoltzfus .
`` What Men Live By '' is a short story written by Russian author Leo Tolstoy in 1885 .
Sharp Objects is a 2006 novel by American author Gillian Flynn and her debut novel .
Dunc 's Halloween is the fifth novel in the Culpepper Adventures series by Gary Paulsen .
The Illustrated Treatise on the Maritime Kingdoms , or Haiguo Tuzhi , is a 19th - century Chinese gazetteer compiled by scholar - official Wei Yuan and others , based on initial research carried out by Special Imperial Commissioner Lin Zexu .
Burning Bright is a 1950 novella by John Steinbeck written as an experiment with producing a play in novel format .
Halting State is a novel by Charles Stross , published in the United States on 2 October 2007 and in the United Kingdom in January 2008 .
Goodnight Opus ( ISBN 978 - 0 - 316 - 10853 - 9 ) is a 1993 children 's book by Berkeley Breathed featuring Opus the Penguin .
Slavery in Massachusetts is an 1854 essay by Henry David Thoreau based on a speech he gave at an anti - slavery rally at Framingham , Massachusetts , on July 4 , 1854 , after the re - enslavement in Boston , Massachusetts of fugitive slave Anthony Burns .
Photometria is a book on the measurement of light by Johann Heinrich Lambert published in 1760 .
The Legend of Drizzt is a series of fantasy novels by R. A. Salvatore that are based in the Forgotten Realms planet Abeir - Toril on the continent Faerûn .
On Heroes and Tombs ( Spanish : Sobre héroes y tumbas ) is a novel by Argentine writer Ernesto Sabato ( 1911 - -2011 ) , first published in Buenos Aires in 1961 and translated by Helen R. Lane in 1981 .
Le Père de nos pères is a novel , by Bernard Werber , released in 1998 .
The Star Trek Concordance is a reference book by Bjo Trimble about the television series Star Trek .
A Mercy is Toni Morrison 's 9th novel .
Bless Me , Ultima is a novel by Rudolfo Anaya in which his young protagonist , Antonio Márez y Luna , tells the story of his coming - of - age with the guidance of his curandera , mentor , and protector , Ultima .
The Fan Club is a novel by Irving Wallace published in 1974 about a group of young men who stalk and plan to kidnap and coerce a popular actress into having sex with them .
The Prone Gunman ( La Position du tireur couché ) is a thriller written by Jean - Patrick Manchette that was published in 1981 .
Fifty Degrees Below ( 2005 ) is the second book in the hard science fiction Science in the Capital trilogy by Kim Stanley Robinson .
Daphne du Maurier 's novel Mary Anne ( 1954 ) is a fictionalised account of the real - life story of her great - grandmother , Mary Anne Clarke née Thompson ( 1776 - 1852 ) .
Zeroville is a 2007 novel by Steve Erickson on film 's upheaval in the 1970s .
`` For the Strength of Youth '' is a pamphlet distributed by The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints ( LDS Church ) that `` summarizes standards from scripture and from the writings and teachings of Church leaders . ''
Britain 's Everyday Heroes is a book by former British Prime Minister Gordon Brown about thirty - three ordinary people whose willing commitment to a cause or a community has informed and inspired Brown .
The Hand of Robin Squires , written by Joan Clark , was first published in 1977 and is now available from Puffin Books .
`` Rapunzel '' ( /rəˈpʌnzəl/ ; German pronunciation : ( ʁaˈpʊnt͡səl ) ) is a German fairy tale in the collection assembled by the Brothers Grimm , and first published in 1812 as part of Children 's and Household Tales .
Forever Odd is a 2005 novel by Dean Koontz , and the sequel to Odd Thomas .
We the Living is the debut novel of the Russian American novelist Ayn Rand .
The Shwezigon Pagoda Bell Inscription ( Burmese : ရွှေစည်းခုံဘုရား ခေါင်းလောင်းစာ ) is a multi - language inscription found on the Shwezigon Pagoda Bell , donated by King Bayinnaung of Toungoo Dynasty and located at the Shwezigon Pagoda in Bagan , Burma ( Myanmar ) .
What a Week to Risk it All is ninth and last part of the What a Week series by Rosie Rushton .
A Universal History of Infamy , or A Universal History of Iniquity ( original Spanish title : Historia universal de la infamia ) , is a collection of short stories by Jorge Luis Borges , first published in 1935 , and revised by the author in 1954 .
The Jack Stapleton and Laurie Montgomery series is an ongoing series of New York Times Bestselling medical thrillers by Robin Cook that follows pathologist Jack Stapleton and his co - worker ( and later wife ) Laurie Montgomery as they attempt to solve the various mysteries that come across their path .
Wraithborn is an American comic book limited series by Joe Benitez and Marcia Chen , launched in November 2005 .
My Late Wives is a mystery novel by the American writer John Dickson Carr ( 1906 - -1977 ) , who published it under the name of Carter Dickson .
The Fudge Family in England is an 1835 epistolary verse novel by the Irish - born writer Thomas Moore .
Faithful unto Death is a work of detective fiction by Caroline Graham , the fifth in her popular Chief Inspector Barnaby series , which has been adapted into the equally successful ITV drama Midsomer Murders .
`` The Moon Moth '' is a science fiction short story by American author Jack Vance , first published in Galaxy Science Fiction ( August 1961 ) .
Stories and Texts for Nothing is a collection of stories by Samuel Beckett .
Foundling Mick ( A Lad of Grit ; French : P'tit - Bonhomme , lit . Lit'l Fellow ) is an adventure novel written by Jules Verne first published in 1893 .
John Inglesant is a celebrated historical novel by Joseph Henry Shorthouse , published in 1881 , and set mainly in the middle years of the 17th century .
`` J. Habakuk Jephson 's Statement '' is an 1884 short story by young Sir Arthur Conan Doyle .
The Gum Thief is Canadian author Douglas Coupland 's twelfth novel .
Thirty Acres ( French : Trente arpents ) is a novel by Canadian writer Philippe Panneton , published under the pen name Ringuet .
The Manzai Comics ( also known as The Comedy Team ) is a manga series written by Atsuko Asano and illustrated by Hizuru Imai .
The Discourse on Reforming the Government of Florence ( Italian : Discorso sopra il riformare lo stato di Firenze ) is a 1520 work by Italian Renaissance political scientist and writer Niccolò Machiavelli .
Introduction to Psychoanalysis or Introductory Lectures on Psycho - Analysis ( German : Vorlesungen zur Einführung in die Psychoanalyse ) is a set of lectures given by Sigmund Freud 1915 - 17 ( published 1916 - 17 ) , which became the most popular and widely translated of his works .
Prisons We Choose to Live Inside is a collection of five essays by the British writer Doris Lessing , which were previously delivered as the 1985 Massey Lectures .
The Game of Chess is a book about chess written by Siegbert Tarrasch .
Eight lines of descent of John Prescott , founder of Lancaster , Massachusetts , 1645 , from Alfred the Great , King of England , 871 - 901 is a book written by genealogist Frederick Lewis Weis showing , as the title suggests , eight different genealogical lines from Alfred the Great to John Prescott .
Weep Not , Child is Kenyan author Ngũgĩ wa Thiong'o 's first novel , published in 1964 under the name James Ngugi .
The Wind Is My Lover ( Swedish title : Singoalla ) is a novel by Swedish author Viktor Rydberg .
Social Theory of International Politics is an academic book by Alexander Wendt .
Breakfast with Buddha is a 2007 spiritual fiction novel by American author Roland Merullo .
Lumen fidei ( English : The Light of Faith ) is the name of the first encyclical of Pope Francis , which was signed on 29 June 2013 , on the Solemnity of Saints Peter and Paul , and which was published on 5 July 2013 , almost four months after his election to the papacy .
Sonnet 147 is one of 154 sonnets written by English playwright and poet William Shakespeare .
Jesus on Mars is a 1979 science fiction novel by Philip José Farmer set on Mars and involving an alien civilization .
Brevis commentarius de Islandia ( English : `` Brief Commentary on Iceland '' ) is a book in Latin written and published in Denmark in 1593 by the Icelandic scholar Arngrímur Jónsson .
Clouds without Water is a poetry collection by Aleister Crowley ( 1875 - -1947 ) , an English author , occult magician , mountaineer and founder of the religious philosophy of Thelema .
A Moving Target is a collection of essays and lectures written by William Golding .
`` The Doctrine of Fascism '' ( `` La dottrina del fascismo '' ) is an essay attributed to Benito Mussolini .
Clear Light of Day is a novel published in 1980 by Indian novelist and three - time Booker Prize finalist Anita Desai .
Bullet Park is a 1969 novel by American Novelist John Cheever about an earnest yet pensive father Eliot Nailles and his troubled son Tony , and their predestined fate with a psychotic man Hammer , who moves to Bullet Park to sacrifice one of them .
`` The Tinderbox '' ( Danish : Fyrtøiet ) is a literary fairy tale by Hans Christian Andersen about a soldier who acquires a magic tinderbox capable of summoning three powerful dogs to do his bidding .
She Came to Stay ( French , L'Invitée ) is a novel written by French author Simone de Beauvoir first published in 1943 .
The End of the Road is the second novel by American writer John Barth , published first in 1958 , and then in a revised edition in 1967 .
Valmiki 's Daughter is a novel by Shani Mootoo published in 2008 .
The Life of Zamenhof is a biography of L. L. Zamenhof , the founder of Esperanto , written in Esperanto by Edmond Privat .
The Red Pony is an episodic novella written by American writer John Steinbeck in 1933 .
Crisis of Conscience is a biographical book by Raymond Franz , a former member of the Governing Body of Jehovah 's Witnesses , written in 1983 , three years after his expulsion from the Jehovah 's Witnesses religion .
Eighth Grade Bites is a novel written by Zac Brewer , formerly Heather Brewer , centered on its main character Vladimir Tod , a vampire from birth .
H is for Hawk is a memoir by British author Helen Macdonald .
The Parasite is an 1894 novelette by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle .
High in the Clouds is a children 's adventure novel written by musician / songwriter Paul McCartney and Philip Ardagh , illustrated by Geoff Dunbar , and published by Faber and Faber in October 2005 .
The Unfortunates is an experimental `` book in a box '' published in 1969 by English author B. S. Johnson and reissued in 2008 by New Directions .
Arnoldi Chronica Slavorum is the continuation of Helmold 's Chronica Slavorum by Arnold of Lübeck .
At Home in Mitford is a novel written by American author Jan Karon .
China Mountain Zhang is a 1992 novel by science fiction author Maureen F. McHugh .
The Card is a short comic novel written by Arnold Bennett in 1911 ( titled Denry the Audacious in the American edition ) .
Published on 15 April 1755 and written by Samuel Johnson , A Dictionary of the English Language , sometimes published as Johnson 's Dictionary , is among the most influential dictionaries in the history of the English language .
Memos from Purgatory is Harlan Ellison 's account of his experience with kid gangs when he joined one to research them for his first novel , Web of the City .
The Anecdotes of the Late Samuel Johnson or the Anecdotes of the Late Samuel Johnson , LL.D. During the Last Twenty Years of His Life by Hester Thrale , also known as Hester Lynch Piozzi , was first published 26 March 1786 .
Ben Singkol is a 2001 novel written by Filipino National Artist F. Sionil José .
Experiments and Observations on Different Kinds of Air ( 1774 - -86 ) is a six - volume work published by 18th - century British polymath Joseph Priestley which reports a series of his experiments on `` airs '' or gases , most notably his discovery of oxygen gas ( which he called `` dephlogisticated air '' ) .
Timescape is a 1980 novel by science fiction writer Gregory Benford ( with unbilled co - author Hilary Foister , Benford 's sister - in - law , who is credited as having `` contributed significantly to the manuscript '' ) .
The Letter from Birmingham Jail ( also known as `` Letter from Birmingham City Jail '' and `` The Negro Is Your Brother '' ) is an open letter written on April 16 , 1963 , by Martin Luther King , Jr. The letter defends the strategy of nonviolent resistance to racism .
The Political Zoo is a book written by the American conservative talk radio host Michael Savage .
Dead Man 's Handle is the title of a 1985 action - adventure / spy novel written by Peter O'Donnell .
Round Heads and Pointed Heads ( German : Die Rundköpfe und die Spitzköpfe ) is an epic parable play written by the German dramatist Bertolt Brecht , in collaboration with Margarete Steffin , Emil Burri , Elisabeth Hauptmann , and the composer Hanns Eisler .
Hunter 's Run is a 2007 science fiction novel written by Daniel Abraham , Gardner Dozois and George R. R. Martin .
The Life of a Peasant Woman ( Житие одной бабы , Zhitiye odnoi baby ) is a short novel by Nikolai Leskov , first published in 1863 's 7th and 8th issues of Biblioteka dlya chteniya magazine , under the moniker of M. Stebnitsky .
The Silent and the Damned ( also known as The Vanished Hands ) is the second novel in Robert Wilson 's critically acclaimed Javier Falcón series , set in Seville .
Have You Seen Tom Thumb ? is a biography of General Tom Thumb written for children by Mabel Leigh Hunt .
I Wish Someone Were Waiting for Me Somewhere ( French : Je voudrais que quelqu'un m'attende quelque part ) is a collection of twelve short stories written by Anna Gavalda .
Way of the Peaceful Warrior is a part - fictional , part - autobiographical book based upon the early life of the author Dan Millman .
The Architecture of the Arkansas Ozarks ( TAOTAO ) is a 1975 book by American author Donald Harington .
`` The Gift of the Magi '' is a short story , written by O. Henry ( a pen name for William Sydney Porter ) , about a young married couple and how they deal with the challenge of buying secret Christmas gifts for each other with very little money .
Torture the Artist , published as Vincent outside the US , is a novel by Joey Goebel published in 2004 .
Emily Climbs is the second in a series of novels by Lucy Maud Montgomery .
In a Strange Room is a 2010 novel by South African writer Damon Galgut .
In the Courts of the Crimson Kings is a 2008 alternate history science fiction novel by American writer S. M. Stirling .
Historietter is a collection of 20 short stories , written by Hjalmar Söderberg .
The Leopard Man 's Story is a short mystery story by Jack London .
The Quest for Cush is a sword and sorcery novel written by Charles R. Saunders , and published by DAW Books in 1984 .
The Children of Zion ( The Path of Agony of the Tehran Children ) is a book written by Henryk Grynberg about `` the fate of the Polish Jews '' .
History of Shit ( Histoire de la merde : Prologue ) is a 1978 book by French psychoanalyst Dominique Laporte ( 1949 - -1984 ) .
The Citadel of Chaos is a single - player adventure gamebook written by Steve Jackson and Ian Livingstone , and illustrated by Russ Nicholson .
The Lays of Beleriand , published in 1985 , is the third volume of Christopher Tolkien 's 12-volume book series , The History of Middle - earth , in which he analyzes the unpublished manuscripts of his father J. R. R. Tolkien .
Al - Istibsar ( Al - Istibsar fi ma ukhtulif fihi min al - akhbar ) ( Arabic : اَلاِْسْتِبْصار فیما اختلف من الأخبار ) is a Hadith collection , by the famous Twelver Shia Hadith scholar Abu Jafar Muhammad Ibn Hassan Tusi , commonly known as Shaykh Tusi .
Fleabee 's Fortune is the first book in the Deptford Mouselets Series by Robin Jarvis ( first published in 2004 ) .
Shadow on the Hearth is the first of three science fiction novels by Judith Merril , originally published in hardcover by Doubleday in 1950 .
Último Volume ( Portuguese for Last Volume ) is a book by Miguel Esteves Cardoso , published in 1991 .
Perilous Dreams is a collection of short stories by science fiction and fantasy author Andre Norton .
Novelas ejemplares ( `` Exemplary Novels '' ) is a series of twelve novellas that follow the model established in Italy , written by Miguel de Cervantes between 1590 and 1612 .
My Official Wife is an 1891 novel by Richard Henry Savage , popular in its day , soon after adapted for the stage , and for silent films in 1914 and 1926 , and a German - language film in 1936 .
GAZ4 The Kingdom of Ierendi was written by Anne Gray McCready , with a cover by Clyde Caldwell and interior illustrations by Stephen Fabian , and was published by TSR in 1987 as a 64-page booklet with a counter sheet , a large color map , and an outer folder .
Bared to You is a 2012 New York Times bestselling erotic new adult romance novel by veteran writer Sylvia Day , focusing on the complicated relationship between two twentysomething protagonists with equally abusive pasts .
Heartsnatcher ( French : L'Arrache - cœur ) is a 1953 novel by the French writer Boris Vian .
L. Ron Hubbard , Messiah or Madman ? , is a posthumous biography of Scientology founder L. Ron Hubbard written by Bent Corydon , which makes extensive use of interviews he conducted with Hubbard 's son Ronald DeWolf .
The Janna Mysteries , a medieval crime series by Felicity Pulman , follows Janna ( Johanna is her full name ) and her quest to find her father in order to seek vengeance for the death of her mother .
A Curtain of Green was the first collection of short stories written by Eudora Welty .
The Noah Conspiracy is a 1981 novel by American writer Michael Shaara , first published as The Herald .
Romance pro křídlovku ( in English : Romance for Bugle or Romance for Flugelhorn ; in German : Romanze für ein Flügelhorn ) is a lyrical epic poem written in 1961 by the Czech poet František Hrubín .
Kurt Busiek 's Astro City is an American superhero anthology comic book series centered on a fictional American city of that name .
' The Jew in the Lotus is a 1994 book by Rodger Kamenetz about a historic dialogue between rabbis and the Dalai Lama , the first recorded major dialogue between experts in Judaism and Buddhism .
Texts from Bennett is a blog created by Mac Lethal ( born David McCleary Sheldon ) , purportedly based on text messages exchanged between Lethal and his `` cousin '' Bennett .
Spirits in Bondage ( 1919 ) was C. S. Lewis 's first published work ( originally published under the pseudonym Clive Hamilton , which is Lewis ' first name followed by his mother 's maiden name ) .
The Right Hand of the Grand Master ( Georgian : დიდოსტატის კონსტანტინეს მარჯვენა , The Right Hand of the Grand Master Constantine ) , also published as The Hand of the Great Master is a historical novel by 20th century Georgian writer Konstantine Gamsakhurdia , who first published it in 1939 in a literary magazine Mnatobi .
Lucy Winchester is a novel by Mennonite author Christmas Carol Kauffman .
Yalkut Yosef ( Hebrew : ילקוט יוסף‎ , `` Collation of Yosef '' ) is an authoritative , contemporary work of Halakha , providing a detailed explanation of the Shulchan Aruch as based on the halachic rulings of the former Rishon LeTzion Rav Ovadia Yosef .
The Blind Owl ( 1937 ) ( Persian : بوف کور‎‎ , Boof - e koor , listen ) is Sadegh Hedayat 's most enduring work of prose and a major literary work of 20th century Iran .
The Indecent Exposure of Anthony East is a 1968 play by David Williamson .
Nineteen Minutes , published on March 9 , 2007 , is a novel by Jodi Picoult .
The Journals of Susanna Moodie is a book of poetry by Margaret Atwood , first published in 1970 .
Address to Young Men on Greek Literature ( alternatively , `` Address To Young Men On How They Might Derive Benefit From Greek Literature , '' Ancient Greek : Πρὸς τοὺς νέους , ὅπως ἂν ἐξ ἑλληνικῶν ὠφελοῖντο λόγων ) is a text by Basil of Caesarea .
Epicurus the Sage was a 2-issue limited series written by William Messner - Loebs , with art by Sam Kieth .
Philip and the Others ( Dutch : Philip en de anderen ) is a 1954 novel by Dutch writer Cees Nooteboom .
Stonewielder is the third fantasy novel by Canadian author Ian Cameron Esslemont set in the world of the Malazan Book of the Fallen , co - created with Esslemont 's friend and colleague Steven Erikson .
The Destruction of Dresden is a 1963 non - fiction book written by David Irving which describes the February 1945 Allied bombing of Dresden in World War II . The book became an international best - seller during the 1960s debate about the morality of the World War II area bombing of the civilian population of Nazi Germany .
Nine Princes in Amber is a new wave fantasy novel and the first in the Chronicles of Amber series by Roger Zelazny .
The Cave Girl is an Edgar Rice Burroughs lost world novel .
Artush and Zaur is a novel by Azerbaijani writer and journalist Ali Akbar ( alias of Alakbar Aliyev ) published in 2009 .
Beatrice and Virgil is Canadian writer Yann Martel 's third novel .
The Last of the Vostiaks ( Italian : L'ultimo dei Vostiachi ) is a novel by the Italian writer Diego Marani .
The Speaker of Mandarin is a novel by British crime - writer Ruth Rendell , first published in 1983 .
Darkworld Detective is a collection of science fantasy stories written by J. Michael Reaves , published as a paperback original by Bantam Books in 1982 .
Day of the Oprichnik ( Russian : День опричника , Den ' oprichnika ) is a 2006 novel by the Russian writer Vladimir Sorokin .
Agaguk is the sixth novel written by Quebec author Yves Thériault .
Little Town on the Prairie is an autobiographical children 's novel written by Laura Ingalls Wilder and published in 1941 , the seventh of nine books in her Little House series .
Liu , Xie The Literary Mind and the Carving of Dragons .
Jack Frusciante Has Left the Band ( Italian : Jack Frusciante è uscito dal gruppo ) is Enrico Brizzi 's debut novel .
`` A Loint of Paw '' is a vignette by Isaac Asimov , first published in The Magazine of Fantasy & Science Fiction in August 1957 .
The Rosy Crucifixion , a trilogy consisting of Sexus , Plexus , and Nexus , is a fictionalized account documenting the six - year period of Henry Miller 's life in Brooklyn as he falls for his second wife June and struggles to become a writer , leading up to his initial departure for Paris in 1928 .
One Clear Call is the ninth novel in Upton Sinclair 's Lanny Budd series .
The Dawning Light is a 1959 science fiction novel published under the name Robert Randall , collaborative pseudonym of American writers Robert Silverberg and Randall Garrett .
Adventures in Two Worlds is the 1952 autobiography of Dr. A. J. Cronin , in which he relates , with much humour , the exciting events of his dual career as a medical doctor and a novelist .
The Discourse on Metaphysics ( French : Discours de métaphysique , 1686 ) is a short treatise by Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz in which he develops a philosophy concerning physical substance , motion and resistance of bodies , and God 's role within the universe .
Written Lives ( Spanish : Vidas Escritas ) is a collection of biographical sketches of famous literary figures , written by Spanish author Javier Marías and originally published in 2000 .
Scrambled Eggs Super ! is a 1953 book by American children 's author Dr. Seuss .
Burke 's Landed Gentry , first published in 1826 and developed by John Burke ( 1786 - -1848 ) , remains widely used by historians and genealogical researchers , e.g. Ancestry.com .
Red Storm Rising is a 1986 techno - thriller novel by Tom Clancy about a Third World War in Europe between NATO and Warsaw Pact forces , set around the mid-1980s .
Deathscent is a children 's novel written by British novelist Robin Jarvis .
Fireworks and Darkness is a 2002 young - adult novel by Natalie Jane Prior .
Rosso Malpelo is a short story by Giovanni Verga , the title ' Rosso Malpelo ' is Sicilian for ' Evil Hair ' , a nickname which combines Rosso ( Red ) with Malpelo ( evil hair ) , as Sicilians believed people with red hair were malicious and had an evil disposition .
God 's Helicopter is a young - adult novel by the American writer Lee Gutkind .
`` La Belle Dame sans Merci '' ( French for `` The Beautiful Lady Without Mercy '' ) is a ballad written by the English poet John Keats .
Year 's Best SF 4 ( ISBN 0 - 06 - 105902 - 1 ) is a science fiction anthology , edited by David G. Hartwell , that was published in 1999 .
`` The Magpies '' is the most famous poem by New Zealand poet Denis Glover ( 1912 - -1980 ) .
A Pack of Lies : twelve stories in one is a children 's novel with metafictional elements , written by Geraldine McCaughrean and published by Oxford in 1988 .
The Survivor and Others is a collection of fantasy and horror short stories by August Derleth , inspired by some of H. P. Lovecraft 's notes left behind after his death .
Mouse Soup is a 1977 picture book by noted illustrator Arnold Lobel .
Feminateek , also known as the Fenomenale Feminateek ( `` Phenomenal Library of Women '' ) , is a collection of 22400 images of female eroticism compiled in 144 volumes by Flemish author Louis Paul Boon .
The Two Pound Tram is a novel written by William Newton ( a pseudonym of Kenneth Newton , a retired doctor ) .
Patterns of Sexual Behavior , published in 1951 , is a work of scientific literature co - authored by Clellan S. Ford and Frank A. Beach .
The Thing Around Your Neck is a short story collection by Nigerian author Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie , it was first published in April 2009 by Fourth Estate in the UK and by Knopf in the US .
Leven Thumps and the Wrath of Ezra is a fantasy novel by Obert Skye that traces the journeys of Leven , a seemingly ordinary boy from Burnt Culvert , Oklahoma , who has now become The Want , Winter Frore , Geth and Clover as they fight to save the Land of Foo .
The Reverberator is a short novel by Henry James , first published as a serial in Macmillan 's Magazine in 1888 and then as a book later the same year .
Red Blades of Black Cathay is a collection of Fantasy short stories by Robert E. Howard and Tevis Clyde Smith .
Outwitting the Devil is a book that was written by Napoleon Hill and annotated by Sharon Lechter .
Mark Twain 's Library of Humor is an 1888 anthology of short humorous works compiled by Mark Twain , pen name of Samuel Langhorne Clemens , William Dean Howells and Charles Hopkins Clark .
`` The Shadow Kingdom '' by Robert E. Howard is the first of Howard 's Kull stories , set in his fictional Thurian Age .
Knitting Under the Influence is a 2006 novel written by author Claire Scovell LaZebnik about three girls in their late twenties who have a weekly knitting circle , yet , they all have busy individual lives .
Gump & Co. ( or Forrest Gump and Co. ) is a 1995 novel by Winston Groom .
`` I taste a liquor never brewed '' is a lyrical poem written by Emily Dickinson first published in the Springfield Daily Republican of 4 May 1861 from a now lost copy .
Johnny Got His Gun is an anti - war novel written in 1938 by American novelist and screenwriter Dalton Trumbo and published September 1939 by J. B. Lippincott .
Samuel Johnson 's Life of Mr Richard Savage ( 1744 ) , short title is Life of Savage and full title is An Account of the Life of Mr Richard Savage , Son of the Earl Rivers , was the first major biography published by Johnson .
In Praise of Idleness and Other Essays is a collection of essays by Bertrand Russell published in 1935 .
Mutineers ' Moon is a 1991 science fiction novel written by American writer David Weber .
An Instance of the Fingerpost is a 1997 historical mystery novel by Iain Pears .
Teresa , el cuerpo de Cristo ( English : Theresa : The Body of Christ ) is a 2007 biopic written and directed by Ray Loriga and starring Paz Vega as the title character , Saint Teresa of Ávila .
Les 11 commandements ( or The 11 Commandments in English speaking countries ) is a French comedy film , made in 2004 , featuring Michaël Youn .
Chathikkatha Chanthu ( Malayalam : ചതിക്കാത്തചന്തു , English : Chanthu Who Never Cheats ) is a 2004 Malayalam musical - comedy film written and directed by Rafi Mecartin , and produced by Lal .
Hero Hiralal is a 1988 film directed by Ketan Mehta and starring Naseeruddin Shah and Sanjana Kapoor in leading roles .
A Yankee Princess is a 1919 American silent film comedy drama produced and distributed by the Vitagraph Company of America and starring Bessie Love .
Niram ( English : Colour ) is a 1999 Malayalam Romantic film directed by Kamal , starring Kunchacko Boban and Shalini in the lead roles .
The Narrow Trail is a 1917 American silent western film directed by William S. Hart and Lambert Hillyer and written by William S. Hart and Harvey F. Thew .

Sweet Alibis is a 2014 Taiwanese comedy film starring Alec Su as a cowardly veteran cop and Ariel Lin as an overzealous rookie .

The Starlit Garden is a 1923 British silent romantic film directed by Guy Newall and starring Newall , Ivy Duke , Lawford Davidson and Mary Rorke .
Man in the Vault is a 1956 film noir about a locksmith , played by William Campbell , who is forced to help gangsters commit a robbery .
Fearless Fighters , also known as Ninja Killers or A Real Man , is a 1971 Hong Kong - Taiwanese wuxia film starring Shaw Brothers Studio veteran actors Chan Hung - lit and Yee Yuen and a cast from Hong Kong and Taiwan .

Patricio G. Espinoza , ( born 1962 in Quito , Ecuador ) , is a journalist best known for his Spanish language investigative TV news reports , newspaper columns and Hispanic community contributions in the United States .
Deborah Poynton ( born in 1970 ) is a South African painter best known for her monumental , hyper - realistic , hyper - detailed , nude portraits , usually of friends and family .
Syed Abdullah Muhammad Taher ( Bengali : সৈয়দ আবদুল্লাহ মোহাম্মদ তাহের)(born 1958 ) is a Bangladeshi politician and former Member of Parliament for Comilla-12 constituency in seventh parliamentary elections from 2001 - 2006 in Bangladesh .
Tanika Liburd ( born 20 May 1982 ) is an athlete representing Saint Kitts and Nevis who specialized in the long jump .
Christopher Soghoian ( born 1981 ) is a privacy researcher and activist .
Pakhi Tyrewala ( born 6 June 1984 ) is the stage name of Punarnava Mehta an Indian actress who debuted in Bollywood in 2002 with Yeh Kya Ho Raha Hai ? , in which she used her real name Punarnava Mehta .
Łukasz Zakrzewski ( born 1984 ) is a Polish sailor , ice sailor .
Iwo Zaniewski ( born 22 May 1956 in Warsaw , Poland ) is a Polish painter , photographer , director and artistic director of Przybora Zaniewski Ltd ( PZL ) , an advertising agency .
Cesare Aureli ( Rome , 1844 -- 1923 ) was an Italian sculptor and writer .
Francisco Combés ( 1620 -- 1665 ) was a Spanish priest who established Christian monasteries in the Philippines in the 17th century .
Jean de Gisors ( 1133 - -1220 ) was a Norman lord of the fortress of Gisors in Normandy , where meetings were traditionally convened between English and French kings .
Bhau Daji Lad ( Ramakrishna Vitthal Lad ) ( 1822 - -74 ) was an Indian physician , Sanskrit scholar , and an antiquary , of the Marathi community , who hailed from a little village in Goa called Parsem who later moved to Mumbai .
Thomas Sills ( August 20 , 1914 -- September 26 , 2000 ) was a painter and collagist and a participant in the New York Abstract Expressionist movement .
Holly Crawford ( born 10 February 1984 ) is an Australian half - pipe snowboarder .
Jake Riviera ( born Andrew Jakeman , February 1948 , in Edgware , Middlesex ) is a music business entrepreneur best known for his management of such performers as Elvis Costello and Nick Lowe and as co - founder ( with Dave Robinson ) of pioneering British indie label Stiff Records .
John Merewether ( 1797 - -1850 ) was an English churchman , Dean of Hereford from 1832 , known also as an antiquary .
Stewart Palfreyman ( born 30 December 1948 ) is a former Australian rules footballer who played for Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the early 1970s .
Moosa Raza was born on 27 February 1937 in Minambur , a small village located between Gingee and Villupuram in the Villupuram District in the State of Tamil Nadu , India to Ghulam Ali Mehkari and Aasiya Begum .
Muhammed Akhtar FRS ( Urdu : محمد اختر‎ ; born 23 February 1933 ) is a Pakistani chemist , and Director General of the School of Biological Sciences , at the University of the Punjab .
Sean Marsden ( born 17 January 1980 in Stirling ) is a rugby union player who was born in Scotland but has spent most of his life in England , being capped by England at U16 Level , even scoring a hat - trick of tries against the land of his birth .
Sir Matthew Lamb , 1st Baronet ( 1705 -- 6 November 1768 ) was a British barrister and politician .
Ann Jago ( born 20 February 1939 in Hull , Yorkshire ) played two Test matches for the England women 's cricket team in the 1960 - -61 season .
Peter Brötzmann ( born 6 March 1941 ) is a German artist and free jazz saxophonist and clarinetist .
Abbas Al - Saffar ( born 15 January 1994 ) is a Saudi Arabian handball player for Mudhar and the Saudi Arabian national team .
Lars Lunde ( born 21 March 1964 ) is a Danish former professional football player , who played in the striker position .
Scott Cardle ( born 28 September 1989 ) is a British boxer who won the British lightweight title in May 2015 .
Colonel John Walpole ( 17 November 1787 -- 10 December 1859 ) was a soldier and diplomat , a younger son of Horatio Walpole , 2nd Earl of Orford .
Sam Savitt ( 1917 - -2000 ) was an equine artist and author , as well as an illustrator of over 100 books .
Kim Kee - hee ( Hangul : 김기희 ; born 13 July 1989 ) is a South Korean footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder for Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors in the K League Classic .
Eirini Aindili ( Greek : Ειρήνη Αϊνδιλή ; born 11 March 1983 in Euboia ) is a Greek rhythmic gymnast .
Richard Sweetman ( born 28 July 1990 in Maitland , New South Wales ) is an Australian speedway rider who rode for several British teams .
Manuel de la Cámara y Libermoore ( or Livermoore ) ( 7 May 1835 -- 1920 ) was a vice admiral of the Spanish Navy .
Andrej Einspieler ( 13 November 1813 -- 16 January 1888 ) was a Slovene politician , Roman Catholic priest and journalist , and one of the early leaders of the Old Slovene national movement in the 19th century .
Cino Tortorella , born 27 June 1927 , is a former Italian television presenter , best known for creating and conducting the Zecchino d'Oro festival of children 's songs .
Jeffrey P. Nadler ( born 27 February 1950 , in Brooklyn , New York ) is a Jewish American Infectious Diseases and HIV / AIDS expert .
Jacques Distler ( born 1961 ) is a physicist working in string theory .
Paul Landers ( born 9 December 1964 ) is a German musician , notable as guitarist for the Neue Deutsche Härte band Rammstein .
Mendo de Benavides ( 1569 - 17 Oct 1644 ) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as Bishop of Cartagena ( 1640 - 1644 ) and Bishop of Segovia ( 1533 - -1540 ) .
Tommy Jessop ( born 19 January 1985 ) is a British actor who has Down syndrome .
Shu - Park Chan ( 1929 - -February 22 , 2013 ) was a Chinese - born electrical engineer who served for many years as a professor at Santa Clara University and went on to found International Technological University and serve as its first president .
Wayne Cegielski ( born 11 January 1956 ) is a former Welsh under-21 international footballer .

Kylie Nicole Sicangco Padilla ( born 25 January 1993 ) , also known as Kylie Padilla , is an Australian--
Edgar R. Aston ( 1847 -- April 14 , 1932 ) was a soldier in the U.S. Army who served with the 8th U.S. Cavalry during the Apache Wars against Cochise .
Ana Boulter ( born 29 April 1976 ) is a British television presenter , who currently lives in Hong Kong .
Eileen Shields ( Born 1970 in New York ) is a footwear designer and owner of the EILEEN SHIELDS label and the Dublin - based store / gallery `` 5 Scarlet Row '' .
William Lowther , 2nd Earl of Lonsdale PC , FRS ( 21 July 1787 -- 4 March 1872 ) , styled Viscount Lowther between 1807 and 1844 , was a British Tory politician .
Esther Qin ( born 18 November 1991 ) is a Chinese - born Australian diver .
Martin Ågerup ( born 1966 ) is a Danish economist and the current president of the think tank CEPOS .
Mohamed Bennouna ( born 29 April 1943 in Marrakech , Morocco ) is a diplomat and jurist from Morocco .
Roman Szymański ( 4 August 1840 , Kostrzyn - 18 December 1908 , Poznań ) was a Polish political activist , publicist , editor of Orędownik magazine .
Fréderike Geerdink ( born 1970 ) is a Dutch freelance journalist and author who specializes in reporting on Kurdish women and political issues in Turkey from Diyarbakir , where she was the lone foreign journalist based there between 2012 - 2015 .
Stephen Duck ( c. 1705 -- 1756 ) was an English poet whose career reflected both the Augustan era 's interest in `` naturals '' ( natural geniuses ) and its resistance to classlessness .
Dorthe Skappel ( born 18 December 1962 ) is a Norwegian television personality , journalist , celebutante and former model , probably best known for hosting God kveld , Norge ! and Gullruten on TV2 .
Adrienne von Speyr ( 20 September 1902 -- 17 September 1967 ) was a Swiss Catholic physician , writer and theologian .
Bernard O'Hara is an Irish historian , born c. 1945 .
Dietrich Nikolaus Winkel ( 1777 -- 28 September 1826 ) was the inventor of the first successful metronome .
Fred W. Stewart ( 1894 - 1991 ) was an American surgical pathologist who was chief of pathology at Memorial Sloan - Kettering Cancer Center .
Michel Tacq , or Mitacq , ( 10 June 1927 -- 22 May 1994 ) is an author of Belgian comics .

Joan Ophelia Gordon Bell ( 1915 - 1975 ) , known as Ophelia , was an English sculptor , known for her several commisisons for the United Kingdom 's Atomic Energy Authority .
Aloha Wanderwell ( born Idris Hall ; 13 October 1906 -- 4 June 1996 ) was a Canadian - American internationalist , explorer , author and filmmaker .
Cecil Wingfield ( 21 September 1893 -- 28 January 1955 ) was an Australian politician and a member of the New South Wales Legislative Assembly from 1938 until his death .
Guru Har Krishan ( ( ɡʊru həɾ kɾɪʃən ) ; 23 July 1656 -- 30 March 1664 ) was the eighth of the ten Sikh Gurus .
Hermann Bahlsen ( born 14 November 1859 in Hannover ; died 6 November 1919 in Hannover ) was a German entrepreneur .
Trần Hoàn , born Nguyễn Tăng Hích ( 1928 -- 23 November 2003 ) , was a Vietnamese songwriter and performer .
Hey You , Pikachu ! , known in Japan as Pikachū Genki Dechū ( ピカチュウげんきでちゅう , lit . a pun on `` Pikachu genki desu '' ( Pikachu is fine ) ) , is a Nintendo 64 video game developed by Ambrella and published by Nintendo that is recommended for children aged 12 and under .
Basketbrawl is a video game released for the Atari 7800 in 1990 and the Atari Lynx in 1992 .
Bible Adventures is a Christian video game by Wisdom Tree first released in 1991 for the NES , and re - released in 1995 for the Sega Mega Drive / Sega Genesis .
The Sims Online ( also known as EA - Land ) was the first massively multiplayer online variation on Maxis 's highly popular computer game The Sims , the second being the Online Weekend mode for The Sims Bustin ' Out , and third being The Sims Social .
Mortal Kombat vs. DC Universe is a crossover fighting video game between Mortal Kombat and the DC Comics fictional universe , developed by Midway Games and Warner Bros. Games .
Flashgal is a 1985 scrolling shooter arcade game by Sega .
Colossus Chess is a series of chess - playing computer programs developed by Martin Bryant , commercially available for various home computers in the 1980s .
Mobiola is a wide range of software by SHAPE Services .
Silent Scope 3 is a rail shooter video game developed and published by Konami .
Philanthropist John Gilmore initiated GNU Radio with the funding of $ 320,000 ( US ) to Eric Blossom for code creation and project management duties .
NCAA Basketball 10 is a basketball video game developed by EA Canada and published by Electronic Arts .
Fast Food Tycoon , also known as Pizza Syndicate in Europe , is an economical simulation computer game developed by Software 2000 , and licensed to Activision Value Publishing .
Bejeweled 3 is a tile - matching puzzle video game developed and published by PopCap Games .
Windows 1.0 is a graphical personal computer operating environment developed by Microsoft .
Cosmic Avenger is a horizontally scrolling shooter arcade game developed and published by Universal Entertainment Corporation and released in 1981 .
Super Swap is an action puzzle game developed by Teyon for the Nintendo DSiWare .
Ultimate Shooting Collection , originally released in Japan as Milestone Shooting Collection :
Kawasaki Quad Bikes is a video game for the Wii console , developed by Data Design Interactive , a budget developer .
Netrek is an Internet game for up to 16 players , written almost entirely in cross - platform open source software .
Gloria Union ( subtitle `` Twin Fates in Blue Ocean '' ) is a tactical role - playing game for the PlayStation Portable , developed by Sting Entertainment and published by Atlus .
Pro / DESKTOP ( commonly referred to as Pro / D ) formerly known as DesignWave , was a Computer - aided design ( CAD ) program from Parametric Technology Corporation ( PTC ) , that allowed users to design and model in 3D and create 2D drawings .
NBA Jam 2001 is a sports Game Boy Color game made by Acclaim Entertainment as licensed basketball simulation for the 2001 - 2002 NBA season .
EA Sports MMA is a fighting video game which was published by EA Sports and developed by EA Tiburon from 2008 to 2010 .
Victoria II is a grand strategy wargame developed by Paradox Development Studio and published by Paradox Interactive , sequel to 2003 's Victoria .
Battle Out Run was a 1989 videogame released by Sega on the Master System .
Windows Server 2008 R2 is a server operating system produced by Microsoft .
Both Outlaw Golf and Outlaw Golf 2 are golf video games developed by Hypnotix , that are intended for adults and mature teens .
Firefly Online is a strategic role - playing video game in development by Spark Plug Games and Quantum Mechanix for Microsoft Windows , Mac OS , iOS , and Android based on the Firefly franchise .
Medieval Mayor is a city - building game set in the Middle Ages under development by Tilted Mill Entertainment .
WINtA is a music video game for the iOS platform , developed pro bono by Masaya Matsuura 's NanaOn - Sha Studio and Triangle Studios , published by ngmoco under the OneBigGame charity initiative .
Supremacy MMA is a mixed martial arts -- style fighting video game developed by Kung Fu Factory and published by 505 Games .
Impossamole is a platform game developed by Core Design for the Amiga , Atari ST , Commodore 64 , Amstrad CPC and ZX Spectrum .
Tony Hawk 's Pro Skater 5 is a skateboarding video game in the Tony Hawk 's series developed by Robomodo and Disruptive Games , and published by Activision .
Sexy Poker is a strip poker video game by Gameloft originally released for mobile phone platforms in 2004 .
F-19 Stealth Fighter is a combat flight simulator developed and released in 1988 ( DOS ) and 1990 ( Amiga and Atari ST ) by MicroProse , featuring a fictional United States military aircraft .
Dvanáct křesel ( Polish : Dwanaście krzeseł , translit . Twelve Chairs ) is a 1933 Polish - Czechoslovak comedy film directed by Michał Waszyński and Martin Frič freely based on the Russian novel `` Twelve Chairs '' by Ilya Ilf and Evgeny Petrov .
Love of Siam ( Thai : รักแห่งสยาม , rtgs : Rak Haeng Sayam , pronounced ( rák hɛ̀ŋ sà.jǎːm ) ) is a 2007 Thai gay - themed romantic - drama film written and directed by Chookiat Sakveerakul .
The Frog Kingdom ( Chinese : 青蛙王国 ) is a 2013 Chinese animated adventure drama film directed by Nelson Shin .
A Season of Giants ( Italian : La primavera di Michelangelo , also known as Michelangelo : The Last Giant ) is a 1990 American - Italian biographical drama television film directed by Jerry London .
Little Miss Sunshine is a 2006 American black comedy drama road film and the directorial film debut of the husband - wife team of Jonathan Dayton and Valerie Faris .
Yeh Zindagi Ka Safar ( English : Journey of Life ) is a 2001 Bollywood film , directed by Tanuja Chandra and produced by Mukesh Bhatt .

Paths of War ( Italian : Franco e Ciccio sul sentiero di guerra ) is a 1970 Italian western - comedy film directed by Aldo Grimaldi .
Maiden 's Rock ( Bulgarian : Momina skala ) is a 1922 Bulgarian silent drama film directed by Boris Grezov and starring Grezov , Katya Syoyanova and Vyara Salplieva - Staneva .
Tonto Basin Outlaws is a 1941 American film directed by S. Roy Luby , the tenth of the entries in the Range Busters series .
The Southern Qi ( simplified Chinese : 南齐 ; traditional Chinese : 南齊 ; pinyin : Nán Qí ) ( 479 - 502 ) was the second of the Southern dynasties in China , followed by the Liang Dynasty .

Belgorod Province was an administrative of the Tsardom of Moscow and the Russian Empire in 1719 - -1775 .
Owing partly to that success , Child World management announced that the new prototype would be used to renovate 11 existing sites , and new market expansion would be targeted in 1990 , 1991 and 1992 using the new design .
The Kerma Culture was an early civilization that flourished from around 2500 BCE to about 1500 BCE in Nubia in present - day southern Egypt and northern Sudan , centered at Kerma , Sudan .
Ordubadsky Uyezd ( Russian : Ордубадский уезд ) was one of the uyezds ( administrative units ) of Erivan Governorate of the Russian Empire with its center in Ordubad from 1849 until 1868 .
The Federation of Independents ( German : Verband der Unabhängigen , VdU ) was a German nationalist and national - liberal political party in Austria active from 1949 to 1955 .
On April 30 , 2010 , Movie Gallery announced it was closing and liquidating all of its stores per a filing of Chapter 7 bankruptcy .
Taiwan under Japanese rule is the period between 1895 and 1945 in which the island of Taiwan ( including the Penghu Islands ) was a dependency of the Empire of Japan , after Qing China lost the First Sino - Japanese War to Japan and ceded Taiwan Province in the Treaty of Shimonoseki .
The Anglo - German Fellowship was a group which existed from 1935 to 1939 and aimed to build up friendship between the United Kingdom and Germany ; it was widely perceived as being allied to Nazism .
Aeromarine West Indies Airways was a United States airline that operated from 1920 to 1924 .
It was founded in 1881 and in 1919 became part of the Union of Post Office Workers ( later to be renamed Union of Communication Workers ) by the merger of the Postmen 's Federation , Postal and Telegraph Clerks ' Association and the Fawcett Association .
Kexholm County ( Swedish : Kexholms län , Finnish : Käkisalmen lääni ) was a county of the Swedish Empire from 1634 to 1721 , when the southern part was ceded to the Russian Empire in the Treaty of Nystad .
East Prussia ( German : Ostpreußen , pronounced ( ˈɔstˌpʁɔʏsən ) ; Latin : Borussia orientalis ; Russian : Восточная Пруссия ) was a province of Prussia from 1773 - -1829 and 1878 - -1945 .
On March 17 , 2015 , Actavis , plc completed the acquisition of Allergan , Inc. in a cash and equity transaction valued at approximately $ 70.5 billion .
The Ulster Transport Authority ( UTA ) ran rail and bus transport in Northern Ireland from 1948 until 1966 .
The Benin Empire was `` one of the oldest and most highly developed states in the coastal hinterland of West Africa , dating perhaps to the eleventh century CE '' , until it was annexed by the British Empire in 1897 .
The Bund Deutscher Frauenvereine ( Federation of German Women 's Associations ) was founded on 28/29th March 1894 as umbrella organization of the women 's civil rights feminist movement and existed until the Nazi seizure of power by the National Socialists in 1933 .
The Taifa of Orihuela was a medieval taifa kingdom which existed probably from around 1239 to 1249 .
Skierniewice Voivodeship ( Polish : województwo skierniewickie ) was a unit of administrative division and local government in Poland from 1975 to 1998 , superseded by Łódź Voivodeship and Masovian Voivodeship .
The Kumul Khanate was a semi - autonomous feudal Turkic khanate within the Qing dynasty and then the Republic of China until it was abolished by Xinjiang governor Jin Shuren in 1930 .

Dr Maressa Orzack studied at Columbia University , where she worked as an experimental psychologist .

Tim Benton ( born 21 June 1945 , Rome ) is Professor of Art History at the Open University in the UK as well as a writer and broadcaster .

Wilfred Watson ( May 1 , 1911 -- March 25 , 1998 ) was professor emeritus of English at Canada 's University of Alberta for many years .
Christa Dürscheid ( born October 4 , 1959 in Kehl - Kork , Germany ) , is a German linguist and professor at the University of Zurich , Switzerland .
Eduard Gaugler ( 23 June 1928 -- 12 April 2014 ) was a German researcher , economist and former professor for human resource management at both the University of Regensburg and the University of Mannheim from 1972 to 1989 .
Leonard Barkan is Class of 1943 University Professor and Chair of the Department of Comparative Literature , at Princeton University .
Mabel Berezin is a sociologist at the Department of Sociology at Cornell University .
Kenneth A. Loparo is Nord Professor of Engineering and Chair of Department of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science at the Case Western Reserve University , OH , USA , where has been affiliated with since 1979 .
David Streatfield is a widely recognized historian of landscape architecture and long - time professor in the Department of Landscape Architecture at the University of Washington .
Marla Spivak ( born 1955 ) is an American entomologist , and Distinguished McKnight University Professor at the University of Minnesota .
In 2003 , Timothy Radcliffe was made an honorary Doctor of Divinity in the University of Oxford , the University 's highest honorary degree .
Shiulie Ghosh ( Bengali : শিউলি ঘোষ , /ʃjuli ghɔːʃ/ , born 28 September 1968 ) is a television journalist , currently working for Al Jazeera English .

Caroline Hawley ( born 1967 , Nigeria ) is a British journalist who has been a Special Correspondent for the BBC News channel since 2007 .
Robert David Stevens ( born 1965 ) is a Professor of Bio - Health Informatics in the School of Computer Science at the University of Manchester .
Michael Schratz ( born 1952 in Graz , Austria ) is an educational researcher , professor of Education at the University of Innsbruck .
Jeremy A. Rabkin ( born July 15 , 1952 ) is a professor of law at George Mason University School of Law , where he teaches constitutional law and international law .
Jia Rongqing ( simplified Chinese : 贾荣庆 ; traditional Chinese : 賈榮慶 ; pinyin : Jiǎ Róngqìng ; Wade -- Giles : Chia Jungch'ing ) is a Canadian mathematician of Chinese origin who is a mathematics professor at the University of Alberta researching approximation theory and wavelet analysis .
Thomas W. Clarkson is a heavy metals toxicologist and an emeritus professor in the department of environmental medicine at the University of Rochester Medical Center .
Margaret Morganroth Gullette ( born 1941 ) , a Resident Scholar at the Women 's Studies Research Center at Brandeis University , is a cultural critic who calls herself an age critic and theorist .
Joseph Fielding McConkie ( April 3 , 1941 -- October 10 , 2013 ) was a professor of Ancient Scripture at Brigham Young University ( BYU ) and an author or co - author of over 25 books .
Catherine Pollard ( born in 1960 in Georgetown , Guyana ) is the Coordinator for Multilingualism for the United Nations .
Heather Cox ( born Heather Schoeny on June 3 , 1970 ) is an American sportscaster who is a sideline reporter for WNBA , NBA , college basketball and college football games on ESPN , ESPN2 and ABC Sports .
Ellen Spertus is a Professor of Computer Science at Mills College , Oakland , California , United States , and a senior research scientist at Google .
Heinz Schlaffer studies German language and culture and is an emeritus Professor of Literary Science of the University of Stuttgart .
Clyde Taylor is an African - American writer and film scholar , who is an emeritus professor at New York University , and a contributor to journals such as Black Film Review and Jump Cut .
Caroline Bilton ( born Caroline Davis on 3 February 1976 in Anlaby , West Hull ) is a British television presenter , currently one of the main anchors host of the BBC regional news programme Look North , broadcast from Hull to the East Riding of Yorkshire and Lincolnshire .
Michael Collie is a British television and radio presenter who appears on BBC News .
Brigitte Mral ( born 1953 in Germany ) is a professor of rhetoric at Örebro University .
Zarin Patel is a British accountant and company executive who was the BBC 's Chief Financial Officer from 2004 , following the promotion of John Smith to Chief Operating Officer , until 2013 .
Richard Conn Henry ( born 7 March 1940 ) is a Professor of Physics and Astronomy at Johns Hopkins University , author of one book and over 200 publications on the topics of astrophysics and various forms of astronomy including optical , radio , ultraviolet , and X - ray .
Edward Kellog Strong , Jr. ( August 18 , 1884 -- December 4 , 1963 ) was an Emeritus Professor of Applied Psychology at Stanford University , who specialized in organizational psychology and career theory and development .
William C. Clark ( born December 20 , 1948 in Greenwich , Connecticut ) is an American ecologist and environmental policy analyst , and Harvey Brooks Professor of International Science , Public Policy and Human Development at the John F. Kennedy School of Government , Harvard University .
Raia Prokhovnik ( born 7 May 1951 ) , is Reader in Politics at the Open University 's Faculty of Social Sciences , for their Department of Politics and International Studies , and founding editor of the journal Contemporary Political Theory .
Catherine Lutz is an American anthropologist and Thomas J. Watson , Jr. Family Professor of Anthropology and International Studies at Brown University .
Linda Ruth Williams ( born 16 April 1961 ) is Professor of Film Studies in the School of Humanities at the University of Southampton , UK .
Lynette Pearson ( 1950 - c. 11 December 2001 ) , known professionally as Lynette Lithgow ) , was a Trinidad - born , British - based newsreader and journalist who is best remembered for her career as a newsreader for BBC News .
David P. Calleo ( * 19 July 1934 ) is an American political scientist , based at the Johns Hopkins University School of Advanced International Studies , where he holds the titles of Dean Acheson Professor and University Professor .
Peter Flora ( * 3 March 1944 , in Innsbruck , Tyrol , Austria ) is an Austrian citizen and taught until his retirement in spring 2009 as a professor of sociology at the University of Mannheim .
Shang Fa Yang ( Chinese : 楊祥發 ; November 10 , 1932 -- February 12 , 2007 ) was an acclaimed plant scientist and a professor at the University of California , Davis .
Theodore Roosevelt IV ( born November 27 , 1942 ) is an investment banker and managing director at Barclays Capital Corporation .
Antony Valentini is a theoretical physicist and a professor at Clemson University .
Rudolf Eitelberger , full name Rudolf Eitelberger von Edelberg ( 17 April 1817 , Olomouc , Moravia -- 18 April 1885 , Vienna ) was an art historian and the first Ordinarius ( full professor ) for art history at the University of Vienna .
Elaine Pagels , née Hiesey ( born Palo Alto , California , February 13 , 1943 ) , is the Harrington Spear Paine Professor of Religion at Princeton University .
Andrew Rossos is Canadian Macedonian historian , Professor at the University of Toronto .
Hermann Hunger ( born 1942 ) , an Austrian Assyriologist , Professor of Assyriology at the University of Vienna , until his retirement ( 2007 ) .
Bernhard Walke ( born 28 July 1940 ) is a pioneer of mobile Internet access and professor emeritus at RWTH Aachen University in Germany .
Allan M. Collins is an American cognitive scientist , Professor Emeritus of Learning Sciences at Northwestern University 's School of Education and Social Policy .
Bob van Asperen has taught at the Royal Conservatory of The Hague and the Sweelinck Conservatory in Amsterdam , while for the past thirty years he has been giving master - classes in Europe , USA and elsewhere .
Annette Kuhn FBA is Emeritus Professor of Film Studies at Queen Mary University of London .
Joel Moses ( born 1941 ) is an Israeli - American computer scientist and professor at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology .
Bruno Zumino ( April 28 , 1923 − June 21 , 2014 ) was an Italian theoretical physicist and emeritus faculty at the University of California , Berkeley .
Dong - Pyou Han , born in Seoul , South Korea , is a former assistant professor of biomedical sciences at Iowa State University who resigned his post there in October 2013 .
Ed Guerrero is an African - American film historian and professor of film and African - American studies at New York University .

The Armadini are a noctuid ( `` owlet '' ) moth tribe of the Catocalinae subfamily .
The Himalayan swiftlet ( Aerodramus brevirostris ) is a small swift .
Amphechinus is an extinct genus of hedgehog of the family Erinaceidae , which lived in Asia and Europe during the Oligocene and in North America , Africa , Asia , and Europe during the Miocene .
The Ural field mouse ( Apodemus uralensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Capricorn lizardfish ( Synodus capricornis ) is a species of lizardfish that lives mainly in the Pacific Ocean .
The Tasmanian pygmy possum ( Cercartetus lepidus ) , also known as the little pygmy possum , is the world 's smallest possum .
The Jamaican owl ( Pseudoscops grammicus ) is a medium - sized tawny colored owl that is endemic to the island of Jamaica .
Nannogomphus is an extinct genus of fossil odonates belonging to the family Gomphidae .
Rhantaticus congestus is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Rhantaticus .
Syngliocladium is a genus of anamorphic fungi within the Ophiocordycipitaceae family .
Agelaia is a genus of Neotropical social wasps ( family Vespidae ) , with species from Mexico to northern Argentina .
Barbapellis pterygalces also known as the Moose eelpout is a species of zoarcid fish found in Southern Ocean .
Notolestus sulcipennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Notolestus .
The Angolan batis ( Batis minulla ) is a species of bird in the Platysteiridae family .
Euperipatoides is a genus of velvet worms in the family Peripatopsidae .
Couch 's spadefoot toad or Couch 's spadefoot ( Scaphiopus couchii ) is a species of North American spadefoot toad ( family Scaphiopodidae ) .
Dorymyrmex ( also known cone ants ) is a genus of ants in the subfamily Dolichoderinae .
The Deccan white carp ( Cirrhinus fulungee ) is a species of freshwater cyprinid fish native to India .
Pinheirodontidae is a poorly known family of fossil mammals within the order Multituberculata .
The Miombo blue - eared starling ( Lamprotornis elisabeth ) , also known as the southern blue - eared glossy - starling , is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .
Stenochlaena is a genus of ferns of the plant family Blechnaceae .
Euophrys is a genus of the spider family Salticidae ( jumping spiders ) with almost worldwide distribution .
The Curimatidae , toothless characins , are a family of freshwater fishes , of the order Characiformes .
The Nyanza swift ( Apus niansae ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
Ailanthus ( /əˈlænθəs/ ; derived from ailanto , an Ambonese word probably meaning `` tree of the gods '' or `` tree of heaven '' ) is a genus of trees belonging to the family Simaroubaceae , in the order Sapindales ( formerly Rutales or Geraniales ) .
The Desertas petrel ( Pterodroma deserta ) is a small seabird in the gadfly petrel genus which breeds on Bugio Island in the Desertas off Madeira .

The Latham 's francolin or forest francolin ( Peliperdix lathami ) is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
The Transcaspian vole ( Microtus transcaspicus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Odaigahara salamander ( Hynobius boulengeri ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family endemic to Japan .
The Hogsback frog or Rattray 's forest frog ( Anhydrophryne rattrayi ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
Hildegarde 's broad - headed mouse or Hildegarde 's zelotomys ( Zelotomys hildegardeae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Fitzinger 's algyroides or the pygmy algyroides or the pygmy keeled lizard ( Algyroides fitzingeri ) is a species of lizard in the family Lacertidae .
The Catostomidae are the suckers of the order Cypriniformes , with about 78 species in this family of freshwater fishes .
The Ramu rainbowfish ( Glossolepis ramuensis ) is a species of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family .
Linisa is a genus ( or a subgenus under Polygyra ) of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Polygyridae .
Monkeypox virus ( MPV ) is a double - stranded DNA , zoonotic virus and a species of the genus Orthopoxvirus in the family Poxviridae .
Jerdon 's baza ( Aviceda jerdoni ) is a moderate sized brown hawk with a thin white - tipped black crest usually held erect .
Cussonia is a genus of plants of family Araliaceae , represented by 20 species .
The Comoro rousette ( Rousettus obliviosus ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae endemic to the Comoros Islands .
Cascaronia astragalina is a species of flowering plant in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Camelpox is a disease of camels caused by a virus of the family Poxviridae , subfamily Chordopoxvirinae , and the genus Orthopoxvirus .
Grauer 's warbler ( Graueria vittata ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Locustellidae family .
Xenion ignitum is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Xenion .
The Saginae , commonly known as the predatory katydids or predatory bush - crickets , is a subfamily of the family Tettigoniidae ( the katydids , long - horned grasshoppers or bush - crickets ) .
Haideoporus texanus is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Haideoporus .
Shaw Mayer 's brush mouse ( Pogonomelomys mayeri ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Beccariophoenix is a genus of three species of Arecaceae ( palms ) , native to Madagascar .
Grossuana is a genus of very small freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae
The Peruvian tyrannulet ( Zimmerius viridiflavus ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Longchengpterus has been assigned to the Istiodactylidae sharing with Istiodactylus tooth form and count as well as a large skull opening .
The Hippoglossoidinae are a subfamily of fish in the Pleuronectidae family .
The VUB night frog ( Nyctibatrachus vrijeuni ) is a species of frog in the family Nyctibatrachidae .
Eucnide ( stingbush ) is a genus of plants in the family Loasaceae .
Mariosousa willardiana , also called Palo Blanco tree , palo liso , guinola and Willard Acacia , is a normally evergreen plant in the genus Mariosousa native to Mexico .

Eburostola amazonica is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Eburostola .
The Woolley 's three - striped dasyure ( Myoictis leucera ) is a member of the order Dasyuromorphia .
The genus Marburgvirus is a virological taxon ( i.e. a man - made concept ) included in the family Filoviridae , order Mononegavirales .
Knipowitschia croatica , the Neretva dwarf goby , is a species of fresh water goby native to Bosnia and Herzegovina and Croatia .
Eporus insignis is a species of beetle in the family Monotomidae , the only species in the genus Eporus .
Broadnose skate ( Bathyraja brachyurops ) is a species of skate in the family Rajidae .
The Singapore blue ( Lampropelma violaceopes ) is a large , arboreal species of tarantula from Malaysia and Singapore .

Ctenomys andersoni , also called Anderson 's Cujuchi , is a species of tuco - tuco native to Bolivia .

The New Guinea naked - backed fruit bat ( Dobsonia magna or Dobsonia moluccensis magna ) is a species of megabat endemic to Papua New Guinea and the Indonesian islands of Waigeo , Yapen , Batanta , and Misool .
The Larut Hills caecilian , Caudacaecilia larutensis , is a species of amphibian in the Ichthyophiidae family found in Malaysia and Thailand .
The Andaman masked owl ( Tyto deroepstorffi ) is a barn owl endemic to the southern Andaman Islands .
Platyla is a genus of very small land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Aciculidae .
The Burmese krait ( Bungarus magnimaculatus ) , also known as the spotted krait or the splendid krait , is a species of venomous snake of the genus Bungarus that is endemic to Myanmar .

The African hobby ( Falco cuvierii ) is a small species of bird of prey in the Falconidae family .
Sanguirana is a genus of true frogs ( family Ranidae ) found in the Malay Archipelago , including the Philippines , the Maluku Islands , Sulawesi , and Seram .
Day 's grass mouse ( Akodon dayi ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .

Sarcosperma is a genus of trees or shrubs in the Sapotaceae family .
The Nava 's wren ( Hylorchilus navai ) is a species of bird in the Troglodytidae family .
Sphex pensylvanicus is a species of digger wasp , commonly known as the great black wasp .
The La Brea poison frog ( Oophaga occultator , formerly Dendrobates occultator ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family endemic to the Cordillera Occidental in the Cauca Department of Colombia .
Hippocampus denise , also known as Denise 's pygmy seahorse or the yellow pygmy seahorse , is a seahorse of the family Syngnathidae native to the western Pacific .
Braulioceras is a smooth , orthoconic orthocerid with very close spaced septa ( around 8 over a length equal to the diameter of the shell ) added to the Sactorthoceratidae in 2007 .
Abbott 's duiker ( Cephalophus spadix ) , also known as minde in Swahili , is a large , forest - dwelling duiker ( small antelope ) found only in a few scattered enclaves in Tanzania .
Polybotrya is a genus of ferns in family Dryopteridaceae .
The California lizardfish ( Synodus luciocepsis ) is a lizardfish primarily inhabiting the Californian coast .
The Malabar woodshrike ( Tephrodornis sylvicola ) is a species of bird in the woodshrike family Tephrodornithidae .
Dendropanax is a genus of flowering plants in the family Araliaceae , consisting of 92 species of evergreen trees and shrubs .
The Guahiba gracile opossum ( Cryptonanus guahybae ) is a species of opossum in the family Didelphidae .
Corsican red deer ( Cervus elaphus corsicanus Erxleben , 1777 ) , also known simply as Corsican or Sardinian deer , is a subspecies of the red deer ( Cervus elaphus ) , endemic to the Mediterranean islands of Sardinia , Italy and Corsica , France .
The Ecuadorian ground dove ( Columbina buckleyi ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .

Ruschi 's rat ( erroneously Rushi 's rat ) , Abrawayaomys ruschii , is a rodent species found in Argentina and Brazil .
Petrotyx is a genus of reef - dwelling cusk - eels .
Rhoptropus is a genus of geckos endemic to Southern Africa , better known as Namib day geckos .
Bowfin ( Amia calva ) are basal bony fishes related to gars in the infraclass Holostei .

The Myodocopida is one of the two orders within the Myodocopa , in turn a subclass of the Ostracoda .
Conostichoceras is an exogastric , breviconic oncocerid included in the family Nothoceratidae , known from the Middle Devonian of central Europe and Upper Devonian of Australia .

Amji 's salamander ( Hynobius amjiensis ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family .
Sawadaea is a genus of fungi in the family Erysiphaceae ( powdery mildews ) .
Cerauropeltis is a trilobite in the order Phacopida that existed during the upper Ordovician of what is now New York , U.S.A. It was described by Pribyl and Vanek in 1985 , and the type species is Cerauropeltis ruedemanni , which was originally described under the genus Ceraurus by Raymond in 1916 .
Lethops connectens , the Halfblind goby , is a species of marine goby native to the eastern Pacific Ocean from central California , USA to Baja California , Mexico where they inhabit kelp forests .
The Bactrian deer ( Cervus elaphus bactrianus ) , also called the Bukhara deer , Bokhara deer or Bactrian wapiti , is a lowland subspecies of Red Deer that is native to central Asia .

Van Zyl 's golden mole ( Cryptochloris zyli ) is a golden mole endemic to the Western Cape Province , South Africa .
The Great Basin spadefoot ( Spea intermontana ) is a species of toad in the Scaphiopodidae family .
Chrysopa is a genus of green lacewings in the neuropteran family Chrysopidae .
The Gorgan salamander ( Paradactylodon gorganensis ) is a species of salamanders in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to a single location in Iran , the caves near the Shir - Abad Waterfall .
Flectonotus is a genus of frogs of the family Hemiphractidae .
The Barrier skink , Oligosoma judgei , is a species of medium - sized skink endemic to New Zealand where it lives in the alpine habitat of the Darran and Takitimu mountains of Fiordland .
Mesocharis is a genus of moths belonging to the Tortricidae family .
Lygistopteroides longipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Lygistopteroides .

The Durango chipmunk ( Neotamias durangae ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
The Caucasian mole ( Talpa caucasica ) is a mammal in the family Talpidae that is endemic to the Caucasus and Talysh Mountains of Armenia , Georgia , Russia , Turkey and Iran .
