The Carpentarian rock rat ( Zyzomys palatalis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Leptoreodon is a small extinct genus of Artiodactyla , of the family Protoceratidae , endemic to North America from the Eocene epoch ( Uintan to Duchesnean stage ) 40.2 - -33.9 Ma , existing for approximately 6.3 million years .
Kladisoceras is an Early Devonian fossil cephalopod included in the nautiloid order Discosorida .
The Congo martin or Congo sand martin ( Riparia congica ) is a small passerine bird in the swallow family .

Pleiarthrocerini is a tribe of beetles in the subfamily Cerambycinae , containing the single genus Pleiarthrocerus and the single species Pleiarthrocerus opacus .

The Leuconostocaceae are a family of Gram - positive bacteria , placed within the order of Lactobacillales .
The Waccamaw fatmucket , scientific name Lampsilis fullerkati , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
The Senegal parrot ( Poicephalus senegalus ) is a Poicephalus parrot which is a resident breeder across a wide range of west Africa .
Hexacosta is a trilobite in the order Phacopida ( family Acastidae ) , that existed during the middle Devonian in what is now Afghanistan .
Lawes 's parotia ( Parotia lawesii ) , is a medium - sized ( up to 27 cm long ) passerine of the bird - of - paradise family , Paradisaeidae .
Columbariinae , also known as pagoda shells , are a subfamily of large deepwater sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Turbinellidae .
The Moroccan rock lizard ( Teira perspicillata ) is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family .
Cerinthe is a poorly studied genus of vascular plants in the family Boraginaceae , known as `` honeyworts '' .
The Mikado pheasant ( Syrmaticus mikado ) is a gamebird in the pheasant family Phasianidae of the order Galliformes , gallinaceous birds .
Eristalinae ( or Milesiinae ) are one of the three subfamilies of the fly family Syrphidae , or hoverflies .
Soochong virus ( SOO ) is a zoonotic negative sense single - stranded RNA virus species of the genus Hantavirus .

Solorina is a genus of 10 species of lichenized fungi in the family Peltigeraceae .
Fusus is a genus of small to large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails and tulip snails .
Ginkgoidae is a subclass of Equisetopsida in the sense used by Mark W. Chase and James L. Reveal in their 2009 article `` A phylogenetic classification of the land plants to accompany APG III . '' This subclass contains the single extant genus Ginkgo under order Ginkgoales , family Ginkgoaceae .
The Antillean euphonia ( Euphonia musica ) is a bird species in the finch family , Fringillidae ( formerly in Thraupidae ) .
The Boulenger 's caecilian , Boulengerula , is a genus of amphibian in the Caeciliidae family .
The Yap flying fox ( Pteropus yapensis ) is a species of megabat in the Pteropus genus found on Yap Island .
Eligmodontia belongs to the subfamily Sigmodontinae and the tribe Phyllotini .
The Dalhousie hardyhead ( Craterocephalus dalhousiensis ) is a species of fish in the Atherinidae family .
Stethacanthus has been further classified as part of the order Symmoriida , a classification that has sparked a controversy .
Thoristella is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Trochidae , the top snails or top shells .
The Atlantic bonito , Sarda sarda , is a large mackerel - like fish of the family Scombridae .
Ferrissia neozelanica , also known as Gundlachia neozelanica , is a species of minute freshwater limpet , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk , or micromollusk , in the family Planorbidae .
Balakata is a genus of trees in the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1999 .
Pratia is a genus of flowering plants in the family Campanulaceae , native to Asia , Australia and New Zealand .
Endorioceras is an extinct genus of actively mobile carnivorous cephalopod of the family Baltoceratidae that lived in what would be North America during the Ordovician from 490 - -479 mya , existing for approximately 11 million years .
Pale rasbora ( Rasbora aurotaenia ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Rasbora .
Enneapterygius namarrgon , known commonly as the Lightning man triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Feeserpeton is a member of the clade Lanthanosuchoidea and is one of the earliest parareptiles .
The Orinoco saltator or Orinocan saltator ( Saltator orenocensis ) is a species of cardinal ( bird ) in the Cardinalidae family .
The Neotropical palm swift or fork - tailed palm swift ( Tachornis squamata ) is a resident breeding bird from Colombia , Venezuela , the Guianas and Trinidad south to northeastern Peru and Brazil .
The suborder Lari is the part of the order Charadriiformes which includes the gulls , terns , skuas and skimmers , with the waders and snipes making up the rest of the order .
Opistognathus lonchurus , the Moustache jawfish , is a species of jawfish native to the western Atlantic Ocean where it occurs in the Gulf of Mexico and the Caribbean Sea .
The Central African mud turtle ( Pelusios chapini ) is a species of turtle in the Pelomedusidae family .
Osgood 's leaf - eared mouse ( Phyllotis osgoodi ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Cauchas is a genus of the fairy longhorn moth family ( Adelidae ) .
The Vietnamese pheasant , or Vietnam fireback , was formerly considered a species of gallopheasant , Lophura hatinhensis , but is now considered a variant of Edward 's pheasant .
The Mindanao lowland forest mouse ( Apomys littoralis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Streptoalloteichus is a genus of bacteria within the family Pseudonocardiaceae that contains two known species :
The California rock lizards are a genus ( Petrosaurus ) of New World lizards in the family Phrynosomatidae .
Pingalla is a genus of freshwater fish in the Terapontidae family .
Nolinoideae is a monocot subfamily of the family Asparagaceae in the APG III system of 2009 .
Adelea together with the genera Adelina and Ithania form the subfamily Ithaniinae .
Tsebona is a genus of the plant family Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1962 .
The Sailfin eel ( Paraletharchus pacificus , also known commonly as the Pacific sailfin eel in Mexico ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
Lobosculum is a genus ( or a subgenus under Polygyra ) of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Polygyridae .
Garra ceylonensis ( the stone sucker or Ceylon logsucker ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the cyprinid family .
The Ailao toad ( Bufo ailaoanus ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Conosapium is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1863 .
Palaeopascichnus is a genus of Ediacaran organism comprising a series of lobes ; it is plausibly a protozoan , but probably unrelated to the classical ' Ediacaran biota ' .
Andaliman ( Zanthoxylum acanthopodium ) is a species of flowering plant in the citrus family , Rutaceae .
Macroscelesaurus is now classified in the therocephalian clade Baurioidea , although its exact position is uncertain .
The Javanese flying squirrel ( Iomys horsfieldii ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
The Gbanga Forest tree frog , Leptopelis bequaerti , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family found in Liberia and possibly Guinea .
The Lord Howe gerygone ( Gerygone insularis ) , is known by many names .
Ceragenia bicornis is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family .
The Virginia opossum ( Didelphis virginiana ) , commonly known as the North American opossum , is the only marsupial found in North America north of Mexico .
The Sumatran flying squirrel ( Hylopetes winstoni ) is a flying squirrel only found on the island of Sumatra .
The Taiwan fulvetta ( Fulvetta formosana ) is a bird species in the family Sylviidae .
Oberländer 's ground thrush ( Geokichla oberlaenderi ) , also known as the forest ground - thrush , is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
Lepidostromatales is an order of fungi in the class Agaricomycetes .
The Prussian carp , silver Prussian carp or Gibel carp ( Carassius gibelio , sometimes Carassius gibelio gibelio and , before 2003 , Carassius auratus gibelio ) , is a member of the family Cyprinidae , which includes many other fish , such as the common carp , and the smaller minnows .
The Jampea Island pipe snake , Cylindrophis isolepis , is a species of snake in the Cylindrophiidae family endemic to Tanah Jampea , Indonesia .
The Congo gerbil or Congo tateril , Taterillus congicus , is a species of gerbil found in Cameroon , Central African Republic , Chad , Democratic Republic of the Congo , Sudan , and possibly Uganda .
The Marail guan ( Penelope marail ) is a species of bird in the Cracidae family .
Pachycereeae is a tribe of 15 genera of columnar cacti in the subfamily Cactoideae .
The Amazonian sac - winged bat ( Saccopteryx gymnura ) is a bat species of the family Emballonuridae from South America .
Sykes 's warbler ( Iduna rama ) is an Old World warbler in the tree warbler family .
Distichoceras is a member of the Haploceratacean family , Oppeliidae , and type genus for the subfamily Distichoceratinae , found in upper Middle and lower Upper Jurassic sediments in Europe , Algeria , India , and Madagascar .
Pliomys is an extinct genus of forest voles , subfamily Arvicolinae , tribe Pliomyini ( Musser and Carleton , 2005 ) .
Purdiaea is a genus of flowering plants in the family Clethraceae described as a genus in 1846 .
The Bradyporinae are a subfamily of the katydid ( or bush cricket ) family Tettigoniidae , which are commonly called armoured ground crickets .
Shinploca shini is a moth in the Drepanidae family and only species in the Shinploca genus .
Godman 's long - tailed bat ( Choeroniscus godmani ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Neocoenyra is an Afrotropical butterfly genus from the subfamily Satyrinae in the family Nymphalidae .
Zoltán Kásás ( born 15 September 1946 in Alpár ) is a Hungarian former water polo player who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Wang Qiu Hong competed at the 2004 Summer Paralympics where as well as being a part of the unsuccessful Chinese 4 × 100 m relay team he also competed in the long jump and won a bronze medal in the F44/46 high jump
Aage Brix ( December 9 , 1894 -- March 16 , 1963 ) was a former U.S. soccer forward who earned one cap with the U.S. national team at the 1924 Summer Olympics .
Zoltán Fodor ( born on 29 July 1985 in Budapest ) is a Hungarian Greco - Roman wrestler , who won a silver medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics in the 84 kg weight division .
Giuseppe D'Altrui ( born Naples April 7 , 1934 ) is an Italian water polo player who competed in the 1956 Summer Olympics , in the 1960 Summer Olympics , and in the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Petra Wenzel ( born 20 November 1961 in Grabs , Saint Gallen , Switzerland ) is a Liechtenstein former alpine skier who competed in the 1980 Winter Olympics and 1984 Winter Olympics .
Göran Crafoord ( born 27 March 1939 ) is a Swedish former sailor who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics .
Sisomphone Vongpharkdy ( born 5 December 1977 ) is a Laotian runner who competed at the 1996 and 2000 Summer Olympics in the 4 × 100 metres relay and the 100 m event respectively .
Aina Berg ( born 7 January 1902 -- 7 October 1992 ) was a Swedish freestyle swimmer who won bronze medals in the 4×100 m freestyle relay at the 1920 and 1924 Summer Olympics .
Bulcsú Székely ( born June 2 , 1976 in Budapest ) is a Hungarian water polo player who played on the gold medal squad at the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Walter Jeandel ( 25 April 1918 -- 4 April 2012 ) was a French cross - country and Nordic combined skier who competed in the 1948 Winter Olympics .
Joe Hamm ( born November 1 , 1950 in St. Louis , Missouri ) is a former U.S. soccer player who was a member of the U.S. soccer team at the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Igor Kanygin ( born 6 June 1956 in Vitebsk ) is a Belarusian former wrestler who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Erich Hagen ( 11 December 1936 -- 26 May 1978 in Leipzig ) was a German cyclist who competed at the 1956 and 1960 Summer Olympics .
Belem Guerrero Méndez ( born March 8 , 1974 in Mexico City ) is a retired Mexican road and track cyclist who represented Mexico at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens where she won a silver medal in the Women 's Points Race .
Božena Dobešová ( October 2 , 1914 -- November 28 , 1990 ) was a Czechoslovak / Czech gymnast who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Jarl Birger Kivelä ( 20 December 1920 -- 27 September 2013 ) was a Finnish diver who competed at the 1952 Summer Olympics in Helsinki , where he finished 13th in a field of 31 competitors in the men 's 10 metre platform event .
Charline Van Snick ( born 2 September 1990 in Liège ) is a Belgian judoka who won bronze in the Woman 's Judo 48 kg in the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Arthur Mannsbarth ( born 28 April 1930 ) is an Austrian former road and track cyclist who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics , and speed skater who competed in the 1952 Winter Olympics and in the 1956 Winter Olympics .
Roberto Moré ( born 11 February 1950 ) is a Cuban former pole vaulter who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Nicolás Uriarte ( born 21 March 1990 ) is an Argentine volleyball player , member of the Argentina men 's national volleyball team and Polish club PGE Skra Bełchatów , was a participant of the 2012 Summer Olympics , silver medalist of 2011 and 2013 South American Championship and Polish Champion ( 2014 ) .
Donato Pavesi ( August 19 , 1888 -- June 30 , 1946 ) was an Italian track and field athlete who competed in racewalking in the 1920 Summer Olympics and in the 1924 Summer Olympics .
Pietro Cunti ( born September 3 , 1962 ) is a former Swiss professional ice hockey centre who last played for SC Bern in Switzerland 's National League A. Cunti has participated as a member of the Swiss national team at the 1988 Winter Olympics .
Endre Madarász ( 8 November 1909 in Szerbittabé ( Srpski Itebej ) -- 3 May 1976 in Budapest ) was a Hungarian athlete who competed in the 1932 Summer Olympics and in the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Konrad Martin Fritiof Svensson ( 2 June 1896 -- 5 March 1961 ) was a Swedish wrestler who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics and in the 1924 Summer Olympics .
Margaret Edwards ( born 28 March 1939 ) is an English former competitive swimmer who represented Great Britain at the 1956 Summer Olympics in Melbourne , Australia , where she won a bronze medal in the women 's 100-metre backstroke in the time of 1:13.1 .
The Jet Set is a Polish R&B duo which consists of English - born David Junior Serame ( South African ancestry ) and Russian - born Sasha Strunin The band represented Poland in the semi - final of the Eurovision Song Contest 2007 in Helsinki .
Abdallah Sidani ( born 1923 ) is a retired Lebanese wrestler who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics .
László Barsi ( 25 June 1904 -- 6 September 1975 ) was a Hungarian sprinter who competed in the 1928 Summer Olympics .
According to some reports , Zhang Jiewen will quit competitive badminton after the 2008 Summer Olympics , when she will marry Malaysian men 's badminton doubles star Choong Tan Fook .
Reginald Flint ( 16 July 1903 -- 1981 ) was an English competitive swimmer and breaststroker who represented Great Britain in the 1924 Summer Olympics and 1928 Summer Olympics , and England in the 1930 British Empire Games .
Tomomi Takahashi ( born 29 January 1956 ) is a Japanese former pole vaulter who competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics .
Jon Eley ( born 19 August 1984 in Solihull ) is a British short track speed skater who competed at both the 2006 Winter Olympics , the 2010 Winter Olympics and the 2014 Winter Olympics .
More commonly known as Wendy Wyland , she represented her native country at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles , California , winning the bronze medal in the Women 's 10 m Platform competition .
Sonia Barrio Gutiérrez ( born December 13 , 1969 in Madrid ) is a former field hockey player from Spain , who was a member of the Women 's National Team that surprisingly won the golden medal at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona .
Zdenko Zorko ( born 18 August 1950 in Zagreb ) is a Croatian former handball player who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics and in the 1976 Summer Olympics for Yugoslavia .
Saša Imprić ( born January 9 , 1986 in Zagreb ) is a medley swimmer from Croatia , who made his Olympic debut for his native country at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens , Greece .
Santiago Lorenzo ( born May 4 , 1978 in Buenos Aires ) is a retired decathlete from Argentina who competed for his native country at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens , Greece .
Elles Voskes ( born August 3 , 1964 in Amsterdam , North Holland ) is a former freestyle swimmer from The Netherlands , who competed for her native country at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles , United States .
Alida Elisabeth Christina Gerritsen - De Vries , born Ali de Vries ( 9 August 1914 -- 20 January 2007 ) was a Dutch athlete , who finished in fifth position at the 1936 Summer Olympics in the 4 x 100 m relay event alongside Kitty ter Braake , Fanny Blankers - Koen and Lies Koning .
During the 1948 Summer Olympics Bob Maas also took a Bronze medal in the Star .
Artur Michalkiewicz ( born September 11 , 1977 in Wrocław ) is a Polish Greco - Roman wrestler who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing and in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Blagoja Georgievski ( born 15 October 1950 ) is a Macedonian former basketball player who competed for Yugoslavia in the 1972 Summer Olympics and in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Ernst Felle ( April 26 , 1876 - -1959 ) was a German rower who competed in the 1900 Summer Olympics .
Nicola Rodigari ( born November 7 , 1981 ) is an Italian short track speed skater who competed in the 2002 , 2006 and 2010 Winter Olympics .
Raúl Córdoba Alcalá ( born 14 April 1930 ) was a Mexican football goalkeeper who played for Mexico in the 1950 FIFA World Cup .
Friedl Däuber ( 5 January 1911 -- 1 May 1997 ) was a German alpine and cross - country skier who competed in the 1936 Winter Olympics .
Edson Alvarado ( born September 27 , 1975 ) is a retired Mexican footballer , who represented Mexico at the 1996 Summer Olympics .
Kurt Moeschter ( 28 March 1903 -- 26 June 1959 ) was a German rower who won a gold medal in the coxless pairs at the 1928 Summer Olympics , together with Bruno Müller .
Wang Long ( born 27 November 1985 ) is a Chinese handball player who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Argyris Theodoropoulos ( born 13 January 1981 ) is a Greek water polo player who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics , in the 2008 Summer Olympics and in the 2012 Summer Olympics .
J. A. Gardiner was a sailor from the Great Britain , who represented his native country at the 1908 Summer Olympics in Hunters Quay , Great Britain .
Cornelis van Staveren ( 14 June 1889 in Leimuiden -- 10 April 1982 , Oude Wetering ) was a sailor from the Netherlands , who represented his native country at the 1928 Summer Olympics in Amsterdam .
Rasoul Amani ( Persian : رسول امانی‎‎ ; born 1 December 1964 in Tehran , Iran ) is an Iranian - New Zealander wrestler who represented New Zealand in Graeco - Roman wrestling in the 63 kg class at the 2000 Summer Olympics ; see Wrestling at the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Heather Moody ( born August 21 , 1973 in Rexburg , Idaho ) is an American water polo player , who won a silver medal at the 2000 Summer Olympics .
José Francisco Jovel Cruz ( born 26 May 1951 in Usulután , El Salvador ) is a retired football player from El Salvador who represented his country at the 1982 FIFA World Cup in Spain .
František Sokol ( February 5 , 1939 -- October 11 , 2011 ) is a Czech former volleyball player who competed for Czechoslovakia in the 1968 Summer Olympics .
August Schmierer ( April 28 , 1870 -- ? ) was a German rugby union player who competed in the 1900 Summer Olympics .
Aleksey Frosin ( born 14 February 1978 ) is a Russian fencer who won a gold medal in the team sabre competition at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney together with Aleksey Dyachenko , Stanislav Pozdnyakov , and Sergey Sharikov .
Kimberley McRae ( born May 24 , 1992 in Victoria , British Columbia ) is a Canadian luger who has competed since 2011 on the Senior FIL World Cup Circuit McRae has also qualified to compete for Canada at the 2014 Winter Olympics in Sochi , Russia .
Henry Seiling ( born May , 1872 , date of death unknown ) was an American tug of war athlete who competed in the 1904 Summer Olympics .
Uno Öhrlund ( born 22 May 1937 ) is a retired Swedish ice hockey player who won a silver medal at the 1964 Winter Olympics .
Georg Hoffmann ( 1880 -- 1947 ) was a German freestyle , backstroke , breaststroke swimmer and diver who competed in the 1904 Summer Olympics and 1906 Summer Olympics .
Zhang Yongjie ( born 11 April 1968 ) is a Chinese sport shooter who competed in the 1992 Summer Olympics , in the 1996 Summer Olympics , and in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
